medical_history.chief_complaint: Assessment of developmental delay, microcephaly, and growth retardation.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms of developmental delay were noted by 18 months of age, with developmental milestones reported as follows: head control at four months, rolling at six months, sitting at 13 months, crawling at 18 months, walking with support at 21 months, and speaking words at 2 years old. The patient was diagnosed prenatally with Tetralogy of Fallot.
medical_history.past_medical_history: History of Tetralogy of Fallot diagnosed prenatally with a Blalock-Taussig shunt performed at 9 months of age.
